<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I suppose one theory of CEO succession is that=
 the next chief executive officer of a firm should be the person who runs t=
he division that makes the most money, that contributes most to the firm, t=
hat is the firm=E2=80=99s intended future. And another theory would be that=
 the next CEO should be the person who runs the division that could=C2=A0<e=
m>lose=C2=A0</em>the most money. If there=E2=80=99s a problem, that guy can=
 fix it! Whereas the guy who runs the consistent moneymaker has had it too =
easy; what does he know about risk?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In general, big modern investment banks want t=
o tell their shareholders a story about some <em>other </em>business =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0asset management, wealth management, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/33155168.256414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmN=
vbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDItMjgvZ29sZG1hbi1raWNrcy1vZmYtaW52ZXN0b3ItZG=
F5LXdpdGgtcmVwb3J0LWNhcmQtb24tY2VvLXNvbG9tb24_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTAyNjIzX01PTkVZU=
1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMx=
MDI2JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBaa8f10db" ite=
mprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"colo=
r: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bor=
der-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #c=
cc;"> retail banking (?)</a> =E2=80=94=C2=A0that offers more stable revenue=
s than traditional investment banking and sales and trading. But if a big m=
odern investment bank is going to incinerate itself in a week, it=E2=80=99s=
 probably going to be in the sales and trading business inside the investme=
nt bank.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-14" style=3D"color: #=
000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-=
bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-col=
or: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[14]</span>
</a>=C2=A0=E2=80=9CEnormous reputational disaster in wealth management=E2=
=80=9D is also a good candidate. Of course <a href=3D"https://link.mail.blo=
ombergbusiness.com/click/33155168.256414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS=
9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMTAvc3RhcnR1cC1iYW5rLWhhZC1hLXN0YXJ0dXAtY=
mFuay1ydW4_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTAyNjIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1f=
c291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMxMDI2JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZ=
