solid; background-color: #ccc;">Financial Times notes</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One immediate hurdle for Pick will be to clari=
fy the optics of an investment banker having got the job ahead of the bosse=
s of Morgan Stanley=E2=80=99s wealth and asset management divisions, its tw=
o major growth drivers.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThe downside is a perceived de-emphas=
is of wealth management within the company,=E2=80=9D said Christian Bolu, b=
anking analyst at Autonomous Research. =E2=80=9CThat certainly to investors=
 is a risk. So I think he has to communicate very early on that wealth mana=
gement is still the driver of the long-term growth of the business.=E2=80=
=9D =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Nevertheless, Pick=E2=80=99s running of invest=
ment banking and his head for risk was seen as a big selling point to Morga=
n Stanley=E2=80=99s board of directors during the selection process, accord=
ing to people familiar with the matter.</p>
</blockquote>
